--->Method execution flow with respect to inheritance :::::
============================================================
When we call a method using Object, first it will check in current class for the method, if available it will call that method directly. If method not available in current 
class then it will check in parent class (it can be direct or indirect parent). If parent having that method then it will call parent class method. If parent class also doesn 
not have method then it will throw exception.   


Note: In inheritance always priority will be given for child class / sub class object. If child class does not contain that method  then priority will be given to parent class method.

