==================
Method Overloading
==================

--> The process of writing more than one method with same name and different parameters is called Method Overloading.

Ex: 

package Polymorphism;

public class Calculator {

	void add(int i, int j) {
			
		System.out.println("sum of first method : " + (i+j));
	
	}
	void add (int i, int j, int k) {
		
		System.out.println("sum of second method: " + (i+j+k));
	}
	
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		Calculator c = new Calculator();
		c.add(10, 20);
		c.add(10, 20, 30);
     c.add(10, 20, 30, 40);// invalid
		
	}	
}


   ---> When methods are performing same operation then we should give same name hence it will improve code readability.
ex ---> 
  
  substring(int start)
  substring (int start, int end)

In method overloading scenario, compiler will decide method should be called . For example,   if we write like below then program will fail it compilation stage .

ex. c.add(10, 20, 30, 40);// invalid


































































































